Modification notice (2026-07-14):

The upstream component was extracted into a standalone Agent Skill named
"url-to-markdown". Public runtime identifiers were renamed, including the
Skill and repository directory, CLI executable, package name, preference
directories, Chrome profile namespace, and environment variable. Legacy
baoyu-prefixed configuration is intentionally not read.

The extraction adapters, rendered-browser workflow, Markdown and JSON output,
and media handling were initially preserved from the pinned source.
Repository-level documentation, install-layout checks, local browser smoke
tests, and Agent UI metadata were added for the standalone distribution.

A subsequent standalone revision removed interactive login and verification
flows, X session-cookie sidecars, and login/interaction fields from JSON
output. Anonymous X capture and the other public-page adapters remain. Chrome
profile and CDP reuse remain available as general browser interfaces and may
reuse state supplied by the user. No automatic upstream synchronization is
configured.

The complete MIT license is included in LICENSE at both the repository root
and inside the installable Skill directory.
